IHC Protocol for Floating Slices (70micron) staining

Day 1
•	Perfuse in 4% PFA .
•	Store Brain in PFA in fridge overnight.

Day 2
•	Slice into 70 micron slices and place up to 2 slices per well into PBS in wellplate
•	Wash slices in PBS, 3 x 15 mins (if done on the same day, 2 more times is enough).
•	Incubate slices 2 hrs at room temperature in blocking solution.
•	Dilute primary antibody in Primary Antibody Solution (normally 1:1000, but varies with antibody).
•	Incubate Slices in primary antibody (200microL per well in a 48 wellplate or 400microL per well in a 24 wellplate) overnight on shaker @ 4°C.

Day 3
•	Wash slices in PBS @ room temperature, 4x at least 30 mins each (the longer the better).
•	Dilute secondary antibody in PBS (1:1000). Incubate slices overnight @ 4°C on shaker.

Day 4
•	Wash slices in PBS @ room temperature, at least 4x, at least 30 mins each.
▪	For DAPI staining: add ~1 μl DAPI in 1 ml PBS for the first wash, leave for ~ 1 hr. 
Alternatively use mounting medium that contains DAPI (easier).
•	Mount.


Solutions:
Blocking solution	Primary Antibody Solution
3% BSA in PBS with 0.25% TritonX-100	1% BSA in PBS with 0.25% TritonX-100
Preparing solution*:	Preparing solution*:
Measure 10 ml PBS in a falcon tube, add 25 μl of TritonX-100. Divide into 2 vials of 5 ml.
•	To 5 ml PBS/TritonX, add 0.15g BSA	•	To 5 ml PBS/TritonX, add 0.05g BSA

*  Calculate the needed amount so you have at least 200/400microL per well. 
